definition.value: The Transfluor assay employs a a beta-arrestin-GFP fusion protein to detect activation of GPCRs: Upon ligand binding the GPCR, cytosolic arrestin-GFP quickly translocates to the cell membrane and then to endocytic vesicles, where it 'clusters' and can be detected by fluorescent image analysis. (Developed / commercialized by Norak, then Molecular Devices)
The property values are divided by the average value for the positive control wells and multiplied by 100: X' = 100*(X/PosAvg)

This is a measurement of how strongly a chemical species attenuates light at a given wavelength. Common units are L/(mol*cm).
The maximum observed fold increase.

The ratio of the concentration of molecule in whole blood (i.e. contains both red blood cells and plasma) to the concentration of molecule in plasma, namely CB/CP.
Ratio of AC50 values
A categorical endpoint is any result that can take one of a limited number of possible values.

Electrical current density is a measure of the density of flow of electric charge; it is the electric current per unit area of cross section. Electric current density is a vector-valued quantity.
The fraction of the bioavailable dose which has been metabolized.
Kp values are defined as the ratio of total concentration of compound in the tissue to total concentration of compound in the plasma at steady state.

A fluorinated 4-methylumbelliferyl phosphate (MUP) derivative that has a lower pKa than that of MUP, making DiFMUP an excellent substrate for continuously assaying acid phosphatases at low pH. The reaction product of DiFMUP has excitation/emission maxima of ~358/450 nm.
alamarBlue is a cell viability assay reagent which contains the cell permeable, non-toxic, and weakly fluorescent blue indicator dye called resazurin.
